4.13. EMERGENCY RESPONSE PLAN

Kraft has instituted an Emergency Response Plan for the facility that divides employees into various management and response teams.  There are in-plant contacts for emergency response which are listed in the Plan.  There are also back-up personnel available in the event that the primary incident response personnel are not available.  At the discretion of the Incident Commander, the Garland Fire Department (GFD) will be called to provide additional emergency responders and equipment.  For all fire emergencies, GFD will be summoned.  In addition, an ambulance always responds with GFD by city policy.  The plan includes information about the frequency and content of employee emergency response training.  Most importantly, the plan contains specific procedures to be followed in the event of a fire or other ammonia emergency.  These include: 



1.    Response to an accidental discharge of hazardous materials or waste;

2.    Notification of internal, external, and regulatory agencies; 

3.    Accident prevention measures;

4.    Procedures to contain and limit the duration of an emergency;

5.    Countermeasures to be employed during an emergency; and 

6.    Procedures to protect emergency responders and other employees. 



